com.bbfos.hbecher.geodiff.geojson

Class GeoJsonIdentifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bbfos.hbecher.geodiff.element.Identifier
      • com.bbfos.hbecher.geodiff.geojson.GeoJsonIdentifier

  • public class GeoJsonIdentifier
extends Identifier
    Represents the unique identifier of a GeoJsonElement.

    If a Feature has a commonly used identifier, that identifier SHOULD be included as a member of the Feature object with the name "id", and the value of this member is either a JSON string or number.
    From RFC 7946, ยง3.2. on the GeoJSON Format

    There are two ways to identify a GeoJsonElement:
    • by the "id" key at its root (cf. RFC 7946)
    • by its properties
    The GeoJSON standard defines the "id" key as what should uniquely identify each Feature, however its presence is not required.
    See Also:
